just_use puzzles.py

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: catalog of (hand, board) fixtures for the decomposition harness

Minimal hand-built scenarios, one per target trick, constructed
to fire that specific trick under CanExtract-respecting rules.
Source stacks are ≥4 (end-peel) or ≥7 (middle-peel); kick-home
stacks for rb_swap are ≥3 and of a valid type.

Helpers: `card`, `hand_card`, `board_card`, `stack`, `hand`,
`base_state`. Adopted by `test_hints_invariant.py` (legacy) and
the puzzle-harness CLI.

## Pointers

- Consumers: `puzzle_harness.py`, `test_hints_invariant.py`.
- DSL fixtures live in `games/lynrummy/conformance/scenarios/*.dsl`;
  that path is the canonical cross-language source. `puzzles.py`
  is kept for ad-hoc Python-only development — not authoritative.
